HEADWORD: Spherule
<hw>Spher"ule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spherula</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sph⟦eacute⟧rule</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
little sphere or spherical body; <as>as, quicksilver, when poured upon a
plane, divides itself into a great number of minute
<ex>spherules</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

